    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "So this is a normal JavaScript behavior. If you attach an event handler on a `<a href` then:\n- the event handler is first ran\n- it opens a new tab if no preventDefault() was called\n\nThis means that we should do something like that:\n\n``` js\nif (event.ctrlKey === true) {\n  // do nothing and open a new tab\n  return;\n}\n\n// else:\n// event.preventDefault\n// do the refinement\n```\n\nIn widgets:\n- menu\n- hierarchicalMenu\n- refinementList\n- pagination\n\nAll of them can or have links in templates\n",
    "created_at": "2015-10-19T13:02:39Z",
